1.  Download Terraform folder and open in VSCode
2.  Sign up for an account in ScrappingBEE via this website: https://app.scrapingbee.com
3.1 Open up secrets.tf and replace scrappingBEE API value with YOPUR OWN API key
3.2  
4. Install the terraform packages
5. Now create an AWS account (it can take p to 1 day to be approved)
[From this step onwards, ensure ur region is US-EAST-1]
6. Go to IAM and retrieve the AWS access key by clicking on your user. It should like something like AKIAXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
7. Set the access key in your terraform profile
8. Initiate Terraform and call terraform apply
[this will take sometime to create....]
9. Once all the services are set up, go back to Visual Studio Code and look for a folder called build
10. Go to a S3 bucket (set as private), and upload the whole build folder into the S3. 
11. Once complete, navigate to AWS cloudfront and attach a cloudfront to the S3 bucket (note the URL after attachment)
12. Go to secrets manager again, you will see a secret facebook_app_id and instagram_app_id
[Follow the following steps]
13. Go to https://developers.facebook.com/
14. Sign up for an account
15. Create a Use case, and select manage everything on your page and manage messaging and content on instagram
16. Once created, go to Tools > Graph API explorer
17. assign permission for pages_show_list, instagram_basic, instagram_content_publish, pages_read_engagement and pages_manage_posts
18. click generate access token then generate page token
19. Replace the page token in your secrets for facebook and instagram respectively
[Now navigate to Amazon Q business in AWS console]
20. click on create app
21. Once created, attach the agent_knowledge_base as the knowledge S3 (go to integrations and select S3)
22. Select single availability index (starter index)
23. DO NOT select anonymous access. Select the $3 subscription model (if not u will be charged $200) - when prompted, create a new user and give it a username
24. Now go to IAM Identity Access center. U can see the username
25. Now when u visit the app, to access Amazon Q, u will provide the login details (click on chat bubble > it will prompt login > login with the details)

